headline: Jabil (JBL) Valuation Check After Raised Outlook and AI-Driven Growth Momentum
summary: Jabil (JBL) just delivered a fourth quarter that lined up with expectations, but the mix under the hood is what matters, especially the momentum in Intelligent Infrastructure and management’s decision to lift full year revenue and EPS guidance. See our latest analysis for Jabil. The upbeat guidance seems to be feeding into an already strong trend, with the stock’s 18.94% 1 month share price return adding to a 64.17% year to date gain and a 5 year total shareholder return of 465.07%.
